history.content:
If you are an undergrad student trying to enroll or wait list for a grad level class, please remember that the enrollment system automatically blocks you from doing so. The error message will say something about the class being outside your 'career'. 

The only way you can get into the class is to ask the instructor for permission to enroll. If the instructor does not yet have permission codes to distribute to you, have them contact cs-enrollments@cs.berkeley.edu to request them.
history.subject: F19: Undergrad trying to enroll into Grad level class? You need instructor consent!
